2NT pass 3C pass 3D pass 3S pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 2, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "8516b3191836ea6301a9263de09e741a99515da1ff3e0d899a88ab578aea1c2f"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/stayman"]
[Student "S"]
{With a balanced 20 points you open 2NT and partner responds 3\C.  

Stayman applies after a 2NT opening, just one level higher. With no 4-card Major you bid 3\D. Partner next bids 3\S.  

Partner is showing 5 \Ss and 4 \Hs. In neither case would you have the 8-card fit you need. So you bid 3NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "W:KJT5.AQJ9.AJ9.KQ A742.862.K.AJT93 Q963.K5.Q875.742 8.T743.T6432.865"]
